<h1>Structure before transformation</h1>

<p>
Many organizations invest heavily in transformation tools.
</p>

<p>
But very little in structural clarity.
</p>

<p>
Transformation fails when the organization itself cannot absorb change.
</p>

<p>
The real question is not which tools we deploy.
</p>

<p>
The real question is whether the structure allows execution.
</p>

<p>
— Patrik Hallén<br/>
Member of Andersen Consulting
</p>

